Nigeria Cement-Makers to Reduce Prices in June, BusinessDay Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-05-27T08:29:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/nigeria-cement-makers-to-reduce-prices-in-june-businessday-says.html
Nigerian cement-makers agreed to
reduce the price of the building material before the middle of
June,  BusinessDay  reported, citing chairman of the Cement
Manufacturers Association of  Nigeria , Joseph Makoju.  President  Goodluck Jonathan  met with officials of the
country’s leading cement-makers on May 17, asking them to bring
down prices within 30 days, according to a statement on the
presidency’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 